# CSS Modules Cursor Rules

## Conventions
- File naming: `Component.module.css` (matches component name)
- Use camelCase for class names: `.headerWrapper`, `.navLink`
- Import as: `import styles from './Component.module.css'`
- Apply: `className={styles.headerWrapper}`

## Best Practices
- DO: Keep styles co-located with components
- DO: Use CSS custom properties for theming (`--color-primary`)
- DO: Use `composes:` for composition between classes
- DON'T: Use global selectors inside modules (defeats scoping)
- DON'T: Use element selectors — always use class selectors
- Combine with `clsx()` for conditional classes: `clsx(styles.btn, isActive && styles.active)`
